# YouTube playlist IDs for the "My Watching" section.
#
# HOW TO USE
# ----------
# The recommended approach is to set YOUTUBE_PLAYLIST_IDS as a GitHub Actions
# repository Variable (repo Settings → Secrets and variables → Variables) and
# YOUTUBE_API_KEY as a repository Secret. That way your playlist IDs are never
# committed to source control, so forks of this blog start with a clean slate.
#
# For local development only, you may create the file
#   config/youtube_playlists.txt
# (without the .example extension) and add one playlist ID per line.
# That filename is gitignored, so it will never be committed.
#
# HOW TO FIND A PLAYLIST ID
# --------------------------
# Open the playlist on YouTube and copy the "list=" parameter from the URL:
#   https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLAYLIST_ID_HERE
#
# EXAMPLE ENTRIES (remove the leading # to activate)
# ----------------------------------------------------
